_Hispa’el_ Active Participle for Regular Shorushim:
The [[{{_hispa’el_ active participle}} form]] has the following conjugation pattern for [[regular shorushim]]:
|            | *Masculine* | *Feminine* |
| *Singular* | מְזַמֵּן <br> _mezamein_ <br> [he is] inviting | מְזַמֶּנֶת <br> _mezamenes_ <br> [she is] inviting |
| *Plural*   | מְזַמְּנִים <br> _mezamnim_ <br> [those men are] inviting | מְזַמְּנוֹת <br> _mezamnos_ <br> [those women are] inviting |
For any regular shoresh, you can replace the letters ‎ז, ‎מ, and ן above with the letters of your shoresh to produce the proper conjugations.
